description:
In March I answered a questionary here at Astrobin and won this LRGB data set from Lloyd at Deep Sky West, which I have now processed. 

Imaging telescope or lens: Astro-Physics Riccardi-Honders 305mm
Imaging camera: SBIG STX-16803
Mount: Astro-Physics AP 1600 with encoders
Guiding camera: Lodestar Autoguider X2
Frames:
Astrodon Blue Tru-Balance E-Series Gen 2: 24x600"
Astrodon Green Tru-Balance E-Series Gen 2: 22x600"
Astrodon Luminance Tru-Balance E-Series Gen 2: 26x600"
Astrodon Red Tru-Balance E-Series Gen 2: 24x600"
Total integration: 16.0 hours
Location: Deep Sky West, Rowe, New Mexico, United States

This was fantastic data virtually without noise but the complexity of the target made it quite a challenge to process, and this is unlikely to be the final version from me.

Comments and Suggestions most welcome
Cheers, GÃ¶ran

Version B: A bit brighter
Version C: A bit more star colour
title: Dreyer's Nebula IC 447
